# The dep unit `xunit_main` also defines a `main`. The port emits every dep
# unit's functions, and any fn named `main` mangles to `z_main` -- so without a
# guard the dep `main` collides with this program's `main` (redefinition). The
# emitter must skip a `main`-named fn when emitting a non-main unit. Mirrors
# compiling zparser alongside zast/zlexer/zvfs (each has its own dump `main`).
main: function is {
    g: xunit_main.greet x: 7
    print "main-g=\{g}"
}
